cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.STAT, cs.CL 

This paper deals with machine learning and classification problems, which are typically covered in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of Hermite polynomials for approximation and the permutation test developed in the paper suggest that the paper may also fall under cs.STAT (Statistics). The real-world datasets used in the paper, such as MNIST and CIFAR10, indicate that the paper may also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
